means: 未改变的，无变化的，依然如故的

sentence.Network_en: Traditional crafts remain remarkably unchanged by the slow incursion of modern ways.
sentence.Network_cn: 传统工艺继续保持原有的特色，没有因现代化手段的缓慢引入而改变。

sentence.Network_en: In Paris and Milan, the dollar opened almost unchanged.
sentence.Network_cn: 在巴黎和米兰，美元开市时几乎没有变化。

sentence.Network_en: In July Belgium's jobless rate was unchanged at 8.2% of the workforce.
sentence.Network_cn: 7月份，比利时的失业率没有发生变化，仍占劳动人口的8.2%。

entry.tran: （一段时间内）未改变的，不变的
entry.def: If something is unchanged, it has stayed the same for a particular period of time.

example.ex: For many years prices have remained virtually unchanged...
In July Belgium's jobless rate was unchanged at 8.2% of the workforce.
example.tran: 7月份，比利时的失业率没有发生变化，仍占劳动人口的8.2%。
